@Workspaces
Feature: Workspaces: Public status and assignees

  To decide which content is accessible as "public" workspaces can be marked as such. All content in a public workspace
is accessible to public users under Drupal's default access restrictions.
Non-public workspaces can only accessed by users with sufficient authorization. This is granted by either
the permission to access all workspaces or by assigning the user to a workspace.

